For decades, Virginia’s racial laws once saw no distinction between Native Americans and African-Americans. It came as a surprise to many that the native americans groups were not protesting alongside the broad coalition of anti-racist activists during the white supremacy rally on August 12th. This article entails the reasons why these local native americans groups have intentionally decided to stay away. 
